  {
    "plataforma": "instagram",
    "external_id": "3912861014782020428",
    "username": "askvinh",
    "nombre": "Vinh Quang Giang",
    "seguidores": 5983960,
    "bio": "Helping you unlock your potential through masterful communication 🚀\nFree 2 Hour Training 👇",
    "descripcion": "Never answer a question quickly.\n\nWhen someone asks you something, the worst thing you can do is rush straight into your answer. Because when you rush, you look nervous. When you look nervous, you lose credibility. And when you lose credibility, your answer doesn't land the way it should.\n\nHere's what to do instead: pause. Take a breath. Let the question settle for just a second or two. That pause does three things. First, it gives you time to organise your thoughts. Second, it signals confidence because confident people don't need to fill every silence. Third, it makes the other person feel heard because you're actually considering what they asked.\n\nMost people think pausing makes them look slow or unsure. It's the opposite. The pause makes you look thoughtful, controlled, and present.\n\nNext time someone asks you a question, try this. Pause. Breathe. Then answer. You'll notice the difference immediately, and so will they.",
